# =============================================================================
# .gitignore.public — used ONLY when publishing to nexus-lab-zen/nexus-lab.
#
# Workflow (see team_memory/iwa/note_2026-04-21_github_public_publish_steps.md):
#   1. Create an orphan branch `public/main`
#   2. Copy this file over `.gitignore`
#   3. `git rm -r --cached` everything that newly matches
#   4. Commit, push to the public remote
#   5. The private monorepo at jk0236158-design/nexus-lab keeps its existing
#      `.gitignore` and is unaffected.
#
# Anything that names a premium template, an internal operations file, or a
# personal-machine path MUST be excluded here.
# =============================================================================

# --- Standard hygiene (mirror of the private .gitignore) ---------------------
node_modules/
dist/
*.log
.env
.env.*
*.env.nokaze
.DS_Store
coverage/
.claude/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/

# --- Premium template source (sold via Gumroad — never publish) --------------
packages/create-mcp-server/templates/database/
packages/create-mcp-server/templates/auth/
packages/create-mcp-server/templates/api-proxy/

# --- Premium build artifacts -------------------------------------------------
dist/premium/
packages/create-mcp-server/dist/premium/

# --- Internal operations manual & shared-ops integration ---------------------
# CLAUDE.md is the operating manual for the AI team. It references shared-ops
# absolute paths and an internal command vocabulary. Not for public consumption.
CLAUDE.md
**/CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
**/AGENTS.md
.mcp.json

# Per-package internal Claude / Agents files inside packages/* (e.g. ops-console)
packages/*/CLAUDE.md
packages/*/AGENTS.md

# --- Internal session logs ---------------------------------------------------
diary/
reports/
knots/

# --- Internal scripts (assume shared-ops layout) -----------------------------
scripts/zen_startup_sweep.sh
scripts/codex-review.sh
scripts/build-premium-zip.py
scripts/publish-premium.py
scripts/memory_lint.py
scripts/memory_lint_assertions.yaml
scripts/test_memory_lint.py
scripts/__pycache__/

# --- Sales/marketing draft material (Gumroad listings, internal checklists) --
docs/gumroad-*.html
docs/gumroad-*.md
docs/gumroad-upload-checklist.md
docs/premium-templates-plan.md
docs/zen-routines.md
docs/ops-console-design.md
docs/ci/

# --- Historical scaffolds at the repo root (empty, predates monorepo) --------
src/
tests/

# --- team_memory / shared-ops state (lives outside repo, but be paranoid) ----
team_memory/
.shared-ops/

# --- Lockfile policy ---------------------------------------------------------
# Keep root package-lock.json (reproducible install for contributors).
# Keep packages/*/package-lock.json where present.
# Premium templates' lockfiles get auto-excluded by their parent dir rules.

# --- Anything else explicitly redacted ---------------------------------------
# Add new entries above with a one-line "why" comment so future maintainers
# know what surface this protects.
